SECTION 2 \'97 COMPONENT A: STAGE JUDGE\
================================================================================\
\
File: backend/evals/stage_judge.py\
\
The judge is an external LLM evaluator that grades pipeline stage outputs \
against explicit rubrics. It runs OUTSIDE the pipeline \'97 it never \
modifies pipeline behavior, only observes and scores it.\
\
Use the same model as the pipeline (gpt-5-nano) for the judge.\
Temperature: 0.1 (low \'97 scoring should be deterministic).\
Use response_format json_schema strict on all judge calls.\
\
------------------------------------------------------------\
JUDGE A \'97 grades MessagingBrief (Stage A output)\
------------------------------------------------------------\
\
Function: judge_messaging_brief(brief: dict, raw_inputs: dict) -> JudgeResult\
\
Rubric (score each criterion 0 or 1, no partial credit):\
\
  containment_clean:\
    All facts in facts_from_input can be traced to a specific \
    input field. Zero facts sourced from generic industry \
    knowledge or training data.\
    Test: for each fact, does source_field exist and is \
    the fact text plausibly derivable from that field alone?\
\
  assumptions_labeled:\
    Every inference is in assumptions[], not facts_from_input.\
    No facts_from_input entry contains words like \
    "likely", "probably", "typically", "usually", "often".\
\
  hooks_grounded:\
    Every hook references at least one fact_id that exists \
    in facts_from_input. No hook stands alone.\
\
  confidence_calibrated:\
    No assumption has confidence > 0.85.\
    Assumptions with confidence > 0.75 have \
    based_on_fact_ids.length >= 2.\
\
  signal_strength_honest:\
    signal_strength matches fact_count and has_research \
    rules:\
      high: fact_count >= 6 AND has_research: true AND hook_count >= 3\
      medium: fact_count >= 3 OR has_research: true\
      low: fact_count < 3 AND has_research: false\
\
  no_prospect_as_proof:\
    forbidden_claim_patterns is non-empty and contains \
    at minimum: "saw your post", "noticed you", "congrats on".\
\
Output schema:\
\{\
  "stage": "CONTEXT_SYNTHESIS",\
  "scores": \{\
    "containment_clean": 0 | 1,\
    "assumptions_labeled": 0 | 1,\
    "hooks_grounded": 0 | 1,\
    "confidence_calibrated": 0 | 1,\
    "signal_strength_honest": 0 | 1,\
    "no_prospect_as_proof": 0 | 1\
  \},\
  "total": 0-6,\
  "pass": true | false,  // pass = total >= 5\
  "failures": ["specific description of each failed criterion"],\
  "warnings": ["non-blocking observations"]\
\}\
\
------------------------------------------------------------\
JUDGE B \'97 grades FitMap (Stage B output)\
------------------------------------------------------------\
\
Function: judge_fit_map(fit_map: dict, brief: dict) -> JudgeResult\
\
Rubric:\
\
  hypotheses_grounded:\
    Every hypothesis.supporting_fact_ids references at least \
    one fact_id that exists in brief.facts_from_input.\
\
  hook_ids_valid:\
    Every hypothesis.selected_hook_id exists in \
    brief.hooks[].hook_id.\
\
  proof_specific:\
    Every hypothesis.proof field either:\
    (a) names a specific customer, metric, or case study result, OR\
    (b) explicitly states "No directly applicable proof point"\
    Fails if proof contains vague phrases like "our product helps" \
    or "companies using this solution."\
\
  why_now_honest:\
    Every hypothesis.why_now either:\
    (a) cites a specific fact_id or assumption_id as the trigger, OR\
    (b) explicitly states "No strong timing signal. Evergreen."\
    Fails if why_now contains urgency language without a cited source.\
\
  ranking_justified:\
    Hypothesis ranked #1 has the highest or joint-highest \
    confidence score. If not, a rank_override flag exists.\
\
Output schema: same structure as Judge A, criteria names as above, \
pass = total >= 4 out of 5.\
\
------------------------------------------------------------\
JUDGE B0 \'97 grades AngleSet (Stage B0 output)\
------------------------------------------------------------\
\
Function: judge_angle_set(angle_set: dict, brief: dict, fit_map: dict) -> JudgeResult\
\
Rubric:\
\
  angles_distinct:\
    No two angles share the same angle_type.\
    No two angles share the same selected_hook_id.\
    Opener entry points are meaningfully different \
    (judge uses LLM reasoning to assess \'97 not string match).\
\
  hook_ids_valid:\
    Every angle.selected_hook_id exists in brief.hooks[].hook_id.\
\
  hypothesis_ids_valid:\
    Every angle.selected_fit_hypothesis_id exists in \
    fit_map.hypotheses[].fit_hypothesis_id.\
\
  why_you_why_now_earned:\
    If any angle has angle_type "why_you_why_now", at least \
    one FitMap hypothesis must have a non-evergreen why_now.\
    Fails if why_you_why_now angle exists but all FitMap \
    why_now fields are "No strong timing signal."\
\
  risk_flags_inherited:\
    If a hypothesis used by an angle has risk_flags, those \
    flags appear in the angle's risk_flags array.\
\
  cta_bridge_natural:\
    Each angle's cta_question_suggestion is a question \
    (ends with "?") and is <= 160 characters.\
\
Pass = total >= 5 out of 6.\
\
------------------------------------------------------------\
JUDGE C0 \'97 grades MessageAtoms (Stage C0 output)\
------------------------------------------------------------\
\
Function: judge_message_atoms(atoms: dict, brief: dict, angle: dict) -> JudgeResult\
\
This is the most critical judge. C0 failures propagate to every \
downstream stage.\
\
Rubric:\
\
  opener_specific:\
    The opener_line cannot be sent to a different person at a \
    different company with only a name swap.\
    Test: does the opener reference something specific to THIS \
    prospect or THIS company? Generic observations about \
    "companies like yours" fail this test.\
\
  opener_simple:\
    The opener_line contains no more than one comma and no more \
    than one connecting word (which, that, because, so, and).\
    If it contains more: fail. The model packed multiple ideas \
    into one sentence.\
\
  value_outcome_not_mechanism:\
    The value_line names a concrete result (a number, a timeframe, \
    a named capability gain) NOT a product feature, mechanism, \
    or action the prospect should take.\
    Explicit failures:\
      - Contains product mechanism words: scoring, tracking, \
        platform, tool, system, workflow, QA, process, cadence\
        WITHOUT a concrete result following them\
      - Is an imperative sentence (starts with a verb commanding \
        the prospect to do something)\
      - Contains bracket placeholders: [Persona's team], \
        [specific verb], etc.\
      - Uses abstract noun stacking: any three of these in \
        sequence: hygiene, pipeline, cadence, process, alignment, \
        SLA, methodology, framework, discipline, visibility\
\
  proof_not_circular:\
    If proof_line is non-empty:\
      - It must describe a result achieved by someone OTHER \
        than the prospect\
      - It must not restate prospect facts (opener facts) \
        as seller proof\
      - It must name a customer, a metric, or a case study result\
    If proof_line is empty string: this criterion auto-passes \
    (honest null is correct behavior).\
\
  cta_locked:\
    atoms.cta_line is character-for-character identical to \
    the locked CTA from the input payload.\
\
  hook_ids_valid:\
    All hook_ids in used_hook_ids exist in brief.hooks[].hook_id.\
\
Pass = total >= 5 out of 6. \
CRITICAL: if value_outcome_not_mechanism fails OR proof_not_circular \
fails \uc0\u8594  force pass: false regardless of total score.\
These two are hard-fail criteria.\
\
------------------------------------------------------------\
JUDGE C \'97 grades EmailDraft (Stage C output)\
------------------------------------------------------------\
\
Function: judge_email_draft(\
  draft: dict, \
  atoms: dict, \
  brief: dict, \
  cta_final_line: str,\
  proof_gap: bool\
) -> JudgeResult\
\
Rubric:\
\
  subject_specific:\
    Subject line is specific to this prospect/angle.\
    Cannot be sent to a different VP at a different company \
    with only a name swap.\
    Not a generic question ("Quick question for you").\
\
  subject_length:\
    Subject line is <= 70 characters.\
\
  no_atoms_violation:\
    Body does not introduce any claim, fact, or proof point \
    not present in the atoms. \
    Judge uses LLM reasoning: "Does this sentence in the body \
    correspond to an atom? If not, it is a violation."\
\
  value_visible:\
    The value_line atom is represented as a distinct sentence \
    in the body. It is not merged into the opener or buried \
    in a compound sentence.\
\
  proof_respected:\
    If proof_gap is true: body contains no proof sentence.\
    If proof_gap is false: body contains a sentence traceable \
    to atoms.proof_line.\
\
  cta_exact:\
    Final line of body is character-for-character identical \
    to cta_final_line.\
\
  no_banned_phrases:\
    Body and subject contain none of:\
    touch base | circle back | synergy | leverage (verb) | \
    game-changer | revolutionary | I hope this email finds you | \
    I hope this finds you | I wanted to reach out | \
    just checking in | quick question | I came across your profile | \
    I know you're busy | I'll keep this brief | \
    Does that make sense | Let me know your thoughts | \
    Hope to hear from you\
\
  no_double_cta:\
    Body contains exactly one interrogative sentence \
    (sentence ending with "?"). That sentence is the locked CTA.\
\
Pass = total >= 6 out of 8.\
CRITICAL: cta_exact and no_banned_phrases are hard-fail criteria.\
\
------------------------------------------------------------\
JUDGE D \'97 grades QAReport (Stage D output)\
------------------------------------------------------------\
\
Function: judge_qa_report(qa_report: dict, draft: dict) -> JudgeResult\
\
Rubric:\
\
  evidence_quoted:\
    Every issue in issues[] has at least one evidence entry \
    that is a quoted snippet from the email draft \
    (not a description of the problem).\
\
  fix_instructions_surgical:\
    Every fix_instruction names:\
    (a) what to change, AND\
    (b) where to find the replacement (fact_id, proof_point, atom field)\
    Fails if any fix_instruction contains only directional \
    language: "make it more specific", "improve the opener", \
    "be more concrete."\
\
  severity_calibrated:\
    No high-severity issue exists for style preferences.\
    No medium-severity issue exists for hard structural failures \
    (missing CTA, hallucinated proof \'97 these must be high).\
\
  rewrite_plan_actionable:\
    If pass_rewrite_needed is true:\
    rewrite_plan is non-empty and each item is independently \
    executable without follow-up questions.\
\
Pass = total >= 3 out of 4.\
\
------------------------------------------------------------\
JUDGE E \'97 grades final EmailDraft (Stage E output)\
------------------------------------------------------------\
\
Function: judge_rewritten_draft(\
  rewritten: dict,\
  original_draft: dict,\
  qa_report: dict,\
  atoms: dict,\
  cta_final_line: str,\
  proof_gap: bool\
) -> JudgeResult\
\
Rubric:\
\
  high_issues_resolved:\
    Every high-severity issue in qa_report.issues[] has been \
    addressed in the rewritten draft. Judge uses LLM reasoning \
    to verify each issue's fix_instruction was executed.\
\
  no_new_content:\
    Rewritten draft does not introduce claims not in atoms \
    or original draft. \
    (Stage E may only remove, replace, or tighten \'97 never add.)\
\
  untouched_sentences_preserved:\
    Sentences not referenced in the rewrite plan are identical \
    or near-identical to original draft.\
    Fails if a sentence that passed QA was rewritten anyway.\
\
  cta_exact:\
    Final line is character-for-character identical to \
    cta_final_line.\
\
  metadata_preserved:\
    preset_id, selected_angle_id, used_hook_ids match \
    original draft exactly.\
\
Pass = total >= 4 out of 5.\
CRITICAL: cta_exact is a hard-fail criterion.\
\
================================================================================\
SECTION 3 \'97 COMPONENT B: EVAL PAYLOADS\
================================================================================\
\
File: backend/evals/eval_payloads.py\
\
Build 30 synthetic payloads covering the full input distribution.\
Each payload is a dict matching the WebGenerateRequest schema.\
\
Payload taxonomy (build at least 2 of each type):\
\
  TYPE 1 \'97 HIGH SIGNAL (5 payloads)\
    Rich research_text, multiple proof points, clear ICP match.\
    Expected outcome: all 7 stages pass, strong atoms, \
    email is outbound-ready.\
\
  TYPE 2 \'97 MEDIUM SIGNAL (5 payloads)\
    Some research_text, 1-2 proof points, reasonable ICP fit.\
    Expected outcome: pipeline completes, atoms may have \
    proof_gap, email is functional but not exceptional.\
\
  TYPE 3 \'97 THIN INPUT (5 payloads)\
    No research_text, minimal prospect notes, sparse proof.\
    Expected outcome: signal_strength = "low", pipeline \
    may fail-closed or produce minimal email with proof_gap.\
\
  TYPE 4 \'97 EDGE CASES (5 payloads)\
    Adversarial inputs designed to trigger known failure modes:\
    - Prospect notes that sound like facts but are vague \
      ("they care about efficiency") \uc0\u8594  tests containment\
    - Proof points that are actually feature descriptions \
      \uc0\u8594  tests proof specificity\
    - Research text about a different company \
      \uc0\u8594  tests fact attribution\
    - CTA final line containing special characters \
      \uc0\u8594  tests CTA lock\
    - Very long research_text (>500 words) \
      \uc0\u8594  tests fact extraction under volume\
\
  TYPE 5 \'97 DIVERSE PERSONAS (5 payloads)\
    Different titles, industries, company sizes:\
    - VP Sales at 50-person SaaS startup\
    - RevOps Director at 500-person fintech\
    - CMO at enterprise healthcare company\
    - SDR Manager at mid-market logistics firm\
    - Head of Growth at early-stage marketplace\
    Tests that persona_cues and hook selection vary appropriately.\
\
  TYPE 6 \'97 EMAILDJ SELLING ITSELF (5 payloads)\
    User company = EmailDJ (the canonical product).\
    Varied prospects across different buyer personas.\
    These are the most important payloads \'97 they represent \
    the actual product use case.\
\
Payload structure for each:\
\{\
  "payload_id": "high_signal_01",\
  "payload_type": "high_signal",\
  "description": "one sentence describing the scenario",\
  "expected_behavior": "passes_all_stages | fails_at_stage_X | proof_gap_expected",\
  "request": \{\
    // full WebGenerateRequest dict\
    "user_company": \{...\},\
    "prospect": \{...\},\
    "cta": \{...\},\
    "sliders": \{...\},\
    "preset_id": "direct",\
    "mode": "single"\
  \}\
\}\
\
Payload quality rules:\
  - All payloads must use realistic but fictional company/person names\
  - No real company names except as proof point examples \
    (and even then, make them clearly fictional variants)\
  - Each payload must have a non-trivial CTA final line \
    (not just "reply to this email")\
  - Thin input payloads must truly be thin \'97 \
    do not add "light research" to make them pass easier\
\
================================================================================\
SECTION 4 \'97 COMPONENT C: EVAL HARNESS\
================================================================================\
\
File: backend/evals/eval_run.py\
\
Command: python -m backend.evals.eval_run [options]\
\
Options:\
  --payloads    all | high_signal | thin | edge | emaildj | <payload_id>\
  --stages      all | a | b | b0 | c0 | c | d | e (which judges to run)\
  --golden      compare against golden set if it exists\
  --raw         enable DEBUG_TRACE_RAW for this run\
  --report      output path for report JSON (default: evals/reports/<timestamp>.json)\
  --fail-fast   stop on first payload failure\
\
Harness behavior:\
\
  1. Load requested payloads from eval_payloads.py\
  \
  2. For each payload:\
     a. Call ai_orchestrator.run_pipeline_single(payload.request)\
     b. Capture: ok, trace_id, subject, body, stage_stats, error\
     c. If DEBUG_TRACE_RAW, load raw trace from debug_traces/_raw/<trace_id>.json\
     d. Extract per-stage artifacts from raw trace:\
          messaging_brief, fit_map, angle_set, message_atoms, \
          email_draft, qa_report, rewritten_draft\
     e. Run each judge against its stage artifact\
     f. Collect all JudgeResults into EvalResult for this payload\
  \
  3. Aggregate results across all payloads\
  \
  4. Write report via eval_report.py\
  \
  5. Print summary to stdout\
\
EvalResult schema per payload:\
\{\
  "payload_id": "...",\
  "payload_type": "...",\
  "pipeline_ok": true | false,\
  "pipeline_error": null | \{code, stage, message\},\
  "trace_id": "...",\
  "final_subject": "...",\
  "final_body": "...",\
  "judge_results": \{\
    "CONTEXT_SYNTHESIS": JudgeResult | null,\
    "FIT_REASONING": JudgeResult | null,\
    "ANGLE_PICKER": JudgeResult | null,\
    "ONE_LINER_COMPRESSOR": JudgeResult | null,\
    "EMAIL_GENERATION": JudgeResult | null,\
    "EMAIL_QA": JudgeResult | null,\
    "EMAIL_REWRITE": JudgeResult | null\
  \},\
  "overall_pass": true | false,\
  "hard_fail_triggered": true | false,\
  "hard_fail_criteria": []\
\}\
\
overall_pass: true only if:\
  - pipeline_ok is true AND\
  - all run judges pass AND\
  - no hard_fail_triggered\
\
